msContents.summary: AM 241 a I fol. is a new shelfmark. In 1996 the shelfmark AM 241 a fol. was divided into AM 241 a I fol. and AM 241 a II fol. and this part was furthermore reconstructed from leaves belonging to three different manuscripts: Ff. 7-15, 18-19, 24, 26-27 and 30-42 originate from AM 241 a fol., ff. 1-6 are taken from AM 249 p fol. and ff. 16-17, 20-23, 25 and 28-29 from Acc. 7 d, Hs. 106.

foliation.p: Foliation on the original parchment leaves only; not the blank paper leaves.

handNote.p: The hand can be identified with the one who wrote AM 45 fol..

history.origin: Written in Iceland c. 1325. It is possible that the illumination was made in Norway. The psalter once consisted of 88 leaves of which only 35 are still extant and ten of them were used as binding material for other manuscripts.
